<Author>keijo
<Content>ok but very boring stayed for 3 nights in a small dbl room. the room was warm, well cleaned, bathroom had a tub and was clean and well functioning too. breakfast was ok, with a decent selection of breads, cereals etc. tv had only german channels and there was no internet available in the rooms.the person in the night watch, in charge of letting late arrivals in, was a bit suspicious and not too friendly, but this might be a language barrier thing too.even though there are all sorts of services in the vicinity, including a supermarket open until 24.00, i found the area around nollendorfplatz very boring. would not choose this hotel if I wanted to experience any culture in berlin. luckily the u-bahn (line U3) station is a stone's throw away, which makes this hotel a option worth considering if you want to be somewhat in the city but have errands at the freie universit盲t campus, which is also on the U3 line.would be 3/5 if they had internets and english-language TV (and if I hadn't found the location so boring.) 
